ect the focus from the individual to corporations, governments, and broader social issues. A compelling study, Hacked helps us understand not just the figure of the hacker, but also digital crime and social control in our high-tech society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aComputer crimesxEconomic aspects. 0aComputer crimesxSocial aspects. 0aHackers. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479898435.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479898435423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479898435/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles